On 20 December, Grenada Government announced the suspension of all flights to the UK until further notice following the new strain of COVID-19 in the UK. Anyone who has been to the UK within 14 days of travel to Grenada will not be permitted entry into the country. Travellers should contact their airlines for further information.
Liat, Caribbean Airlines and Inter Caribbean operate from Grenada to Barbados where flights to the UK are still available.
If you are considering travelling by any indirect routes you are responsible for ensuring that you meet all requirements for entry and onward travel of all countries and territories that you transit. Review the relevant country pages on FCDO Travel Advice before travel and check carefully any requirements for COVID testing before departure, to ensure that your test certificate, if required, will be accepted in your transit and arrival country.
Returning to the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK. From 10 July those entering the UK from Grenada will not have to self- isolate on arrival.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission in Bridgetown, Barbados, on Facebook and Twitter.
